        "queries": [
          "v1",
          "v2"
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "group=v1 kinds=CronJob,Pod\ngroup=v2 kinds=\n"
    }
  ]
}

Here are the public test cases for feature9_version_processable:
{
  "description": "Classifies whether an API group identifier matches a getter's version shape. A core getter accepts a bare single-segment version with no slash and rejects a slashed group/version, a lone slash, and an empty string. A regular getter is the mirror image: it accepts a group/version pair containing exactly one slash and rejects a bare version, a lone slash, and an empty string. Each query prints a line with the quoted input and a 'processable=' boolean.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "version_processable",
        "style": "core",
        "group_version": "v1",
        "kinds": [
          "Pod",
          "CronJob"
        ],
        "queries": [
          "v1",
          "app/v1",
          "/",
          ""
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "group='v1' processable=true\ngroup='app/v1' processable=false\ngroup='/' processable=false\ngroup='' processable=false\n"
    }
  ]
}

